<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Ianladarr</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-18 13:10:57</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>+Mana items can be just as good as +wisdom items.  1 wisdom give 10 mana at lvl 50 and as the levels go down, the less mana it gives.  However, +Mana items always give the same amount of mana, making them just as good, and even better than wis items at low levels.<BR>
<BR>
But there are less +mana items than +wis items.  Here's another thing to think about... after you have 200 wisdom, each point of wisdom extra only gives 1 mana!!!! <BR>
 (at lvl 50)(note that all the numbers are at lvl 50) <BR>
If the item has both wisdom and mana (Tunarian Scimitar) then the number reflected is the total  - ie +10 wis for +6 wis and +40 mana at level 50 <BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
